description:
when creating multiple server with min_count/max_count, the response only has one server's info, as follow:

{
    "server": {
      "id": "11f8d434-cee0-45e2-8f24-d9b13403af16",
      "links": [
        {
          "href": "http://localhost:8774/v2/ff2f74b28d274a3489a5cbb196cdd36c/servers/11f8d434-cee0-45e2-8f24-d9b13403af16",
          "rel": "self"
        },
        {
          "href": "http://localhost:8774/ff2f74b28d274a3489a5cbb196cdd36c/servers/11f8d434-cee0-45e2-8f24-d9b13403af16",
          "rel": "bookmark"
        }
      ],
      "adminPass": "jFYiGXPSU483"
    }
  }
}

This may be a headache if someone wants to do something for every newly created server, and I think it is also a good design to get what you request, the better response may be like:

{
    "servers": []
}

or

[
    {"server": {}}
    {"server": {}}
]

any ideas?

comments.content:
when creating multiple server with min_count/max_count, the response only has one server's info, as follow:

{
    "server": {
      "id": "11f8d434-cee0-45e2-8f24-d9b13403af16",
      "links": [
        {
          "href": "http://localhost:8774/v2/ff2f74b28d274a3489a5cbb196cdd36c/servers/11f8d434-cee0-45e2-8f24-d9b13403af16",
          "rel": "self"
        },
        {
          "href": "http://localhost:8774/ff2f74b28d274a3489a5cbb196cdd36c/servers/11f8d434-cee0-45e2-8f24-d9b13403af16",
          "rel": "bookmark"
        }
      ],
      "adminPass": "jFYiGXPSU483"
    }
  }
}

This may be a headache if someone wants to do something for every newly created server, and I think it is also  a good design to get what you request.
